track_notes: WARNING this route follows a path that skirts the top of the cliffs at Craig Maesglase.  Great views but caution needed. If in doubt keep further left (west) around the top of the corrie. Park just before river bridge, space for a couple of cars. Walk a back up hill to gateway and follow good farm track south. This becomes a path (boggy in places) before climbing steeply to where it flattens at the top. Bear right (north) onto indistinct paths that skirt the top of Craig Maesglase (see warning above) before leveling and turning left (west) to the summit. Stiles on fences on this route.

This route avoids the cliff edge at Craig Maesglase, but also loses the view into the corrie. Slightly shorter and more direct, but more boggy. Park just before river bridge, space for a couple of cars. Walk a back up hill to gateway and follow good farm track south. This becomes a path (boggy in places) before climbing steeply to where it flattens at the top. Continue to fence line and turn right up hill again, following fence on your left. Boggy sections to skirt around. Stile near summit.

Total time (including ops): 3hr 20m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
